    <item>
      <title>Negroni</title>
      <link>https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/drinks/negroni/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 12 Jan 2018 21:27:58 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/drinks/negroni/</guid>
      <description>The Negroni is my favorite drink. It’s quite sweet, but also bitter and complex. I make mine with Tanquery gin and Cocci di Torino vermouth. It can also be served on the rocks, but I prefer it neat. 1 oz London dry gin1 oz Campari1 oz Sweet vermouth Add all ingredients to a shaker along with plenty of ice. Stir for 15–20 seconds. Strain into a coupe glass.
Garnish with an orange peel.</description>
    </item>
    
