    <item>
      <title>Vermouth</title>
      <link>https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/ingredients/vermouth/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 08 Jan 2018 13:09:24 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://sidecar.keithjgrant.com/ingredients/vermouth/</guid>
      <description>Types There are several types of vermouth, the most common being ”dry” and “sweet”. Dry vermouth is known for its use in a martini.
Brands The Martini &amp;amp; Rossi brand is the most readily available in the United States. Their dry vermouth is passable. But I find their sweet (called “Rosso”) to be medicinal and a quick way to ruin a drink.</description>
